abstracts.cdata!:
The Phosphate Fertilizer Project
            consists of: (a) the erection of a plant, near the port of
            Safi, to produce for export 371,250 tons per year of
            phosphoric acid and 225,780 tons per year of monoammonium
            phosphate; (b) facilities at the plant and at the port of
            Safi for the supply of utilities, the transportation and
            storage of raw materials and finished products.
